## Four-Beat Caption Structure (follow strictly)

**Beat 1 — Drop-in (30-50 words)**
Open with "POV: You're [{{ pov_type }}]. [Specific time/setting/what you're doing]."
Make it visual and specific: Friday at 4:52 PM, coffee going cold, about to close your laptop.
No intro, no context-setting — throw the reader straight into the scene.

**Beat 2 — The Anomaly (50-70 words)**
A specific, concrete anomaly appears. Include the technical detail ({{ technical_detail }}) but don't explain it yet — mirror the real feeling of noticing something wrong without yet understanding it. Hold the suspense for one beat.

**Beat 3 — The Reveal (60-80 words)**
Explain what the signal means ({{ attack_type }}) using a concrete real-world analogy. Give one action the reader can take right now ({{ defense_action }}). The lesson must be memorable and specific — not just "be careful."

**Beat 4 — Engagement close (20-40 words)**
Pick one hook from below. Close naturally.
End with: {{ cta }}
Tags: {{ default_tags | join(' ') }} plus 2 tags relevant to this attack type.

## Engagement Hooks (pick one, ranked by performance)

**Tier 1 — Identity/action (highest comment rate):**
- "What's your first move in this situation? Drop it below 👇"
- "Have you ever spotted something like this? What did you do?"
- "Seeing that [specific artifact] — do you disconnect first, or keep watching the logs?"

**Tier 2 — Knowledge check (highest save rate):**
- "Save this so you recognize it when it happens to you."
- "Would you have caught this in your own network? Be honest 👇"

**Do NOT use:**
- Follow/share/like bait of any kind
- Specific real employee names or internal system paths
- Complete exploit payloads or step-by-step attack instructions
